Package suncertify.ui

This package makes up the the presentation layer of the application.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ContractorModel
    ContractorModel extends the TableModel interfaces and specifies extra methods that the ContractorTable table will need for interacting with the custom contractor data model.
    LaunchManager
    LaunchManager defines useful method definitions for launching and configuring the application.
    WindowManager
    WindowManager is the common interface for all UI frames in the application.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractWindow
    AbstractWindow is the common superclass of all frames used in the application and a subclass of JFrame.
    ClientConfigWindow
    The class ClientConfigWindow is responsible for configuring and launching the main application window, the ClientWindow, when the system is run in Networked Mode.
    ClientWindow
    The class ClientWindow is direct subclass of AbstractWindow and acts as the main UI window for the application.
    CliLauncher
    The class CliLauncher is responsible for launching the application using a command line interface.
    ContractorTable
    The class ContractorTable is a subclass of JTable responsible for displaying contractor records.
    ContractorTableModel
    The class ContractorTableModel is subclass of AbstractTableModel responsible for providing the ContractorTable with the method implementations necessary to interrogate the tabular data model provided, in this case, a List of Contractor objects.
    DatabaseFileChooser
    The class DatabaseFileChooser is a subclass of JFileChooser responsible for providing the user with an easy, user-friendly way of selecting a database file during configuration of the system on start-up.
    Messages
    The class Messages defines all the titles, labels, tooltips, button texts, and any other messages displayed to the user through the GUI.
    ServerConfigWindow
    The class ClientConfigWindow is responsible for configuring and launching the main application window, the ClientWindow, when the system is run in non-Networked Mode.
    StandaloneConfigWindow
    The class StandaloneConfigWindow is responsible for configuring and launching the RMI server, when the system is run in Networked Mode.

Package suncertify.ui Description

This package makes up the the presentation layer of the application. It's responsible for providing the user with a GUI interface so they can configure and use the application. It also contains the CliLauncher class, which contains the main method enables the application to be launched from the command line.
